<subSubSection id="B2A26505FFFF140E6AD34DC7FB681179" pageId="2" pageNumber="346" type="description">
<paragraph id="FA07368EFFFF140E6AD34DC7FEBA12A9" blockId="2.[151,663,1122,1184]" box="[151,280,1158,1184]" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">
(
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6AE44DC7FEB212A9" box="[160,272,1158,1184]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1A–J</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA07368EFFFF140E6AD34D8FFE4A12E1" blockId="2.[151,1437,1230,1977]" box="[151,488,1230,1256]" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis id="C8CCEA9CFFFF140E6AD34D8FFEE112E1" bold="true" box="[151,323,1230,1256]" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Measurement.</emphasis>
Male: 
<quantity id="3D409B6BFFFF140E6BD64D8FFE4612E1" box="[402,484,1230,1256]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="346" unit="mm" value="3.9">3.9mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA07368EFFFF140E6A834DB3FE6413ED" blockId="2.[151,1437,1230,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis id="C8CCEA9CFFFF140E6A834DB3FEFB1305" bold="true" box="[199,345,1266,1292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Description.</emphasis>
Coloration. General color chocolate brown (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E69114DB3FC711305" box="[853,979,1266,1292]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1A–D</figureCitation>
). Crown anterior portion black with two conspicuous black spots normally present in middle adjacent to eyes (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E69E64C57FB8B1339" box="[930,1065,1302,1328]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1A, 1C</figureCitation>
). Eye reddish brown, surrounded with yellow band (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6B284C7BFE48135D" box="[364,490,1338,1364]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1A–D</figureCitation>
). Face black with yellowish patch on frontoclypeus (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6E044C7BFB38135D" box="[1088,1178,1338,1364]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with black band along the anterior margin, whitish across the middle while yellowish brown at the posterior margin (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6F7A4C1FFF181395" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1A, 1C</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum and scutellum yellowish brown (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E68964CC3FCFF1395" box="[722,861,1410,1436]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1A, 1C</figureCitation>
). Thorax and abdomen black in ventral and lateral view (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6A994CE7FE9113C9" box="[221,307,1446,1472]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Abdominal segments separated by yellowish bands (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E69D64CE7FC4A13C9" box="[914,1000,1446,1472]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Forewing dark brownish with prominent venation (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6B7A4C8BFE1B13ED" box="[318,441,1482,1508]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA07368EFFFF140E6A834CAFFC0310B5" blockId="2.[151,1437,1230,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">
Morphology. Crown narrower than pronotum, with anterior margin slightly angulate and smoothly curved to face (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6A924F53FEF71025" box="[214,341,1554,1580]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1A–D</figureCitation>
). Crown almost equal to or a little longer than breadth between eyes (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6E2A4F53FB5A1025" box="[1134,1272,1554,1580]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1A, 1C</figureCitation>
). Ocellus next to eye slightly below anterior margin of crown (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E68854F77FCEC1059" box="[705,846,1590,1616]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1B, 1D</figureCitation>
). Antennae long and thin. Face slightly longer than broad (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6AA14F1BFE9F107D" box="[229,317,1626,1652]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Pronotum median length a little smaller than median length of crown with posterior margin slightly concave (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6B414F3FFE331091" box="[261,401,1662,1688]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1A, 1C</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum and scutellum generally shorter than pronotum. Scutellum with a transverse impression in middle (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6BD74FE3FE4810B5" box="[403,490,1698,1724]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Forewing macropterous (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E695D4FE3FC3610B5" box="[793,916,1698,1724]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA07368EFFFF140E6A834F87FB681179" blockId="2.[151,1437,1230,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">
Male genitalia. Pygofer lobe broad basally with apex truncate (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E69C14F87FC7810E9" box="[901,986,1734,1760]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Pygofer side with few dorsal macrosetae (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6A824FABFEB8110D" box="[198,282,1770,1796]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate large, triangular, with a row of uniseriate macrosetae (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6E7A4FABFB33110D" box="[1086,1169,1770,1796]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Valve triangular. Style narrow with digitate apophysis, laterally curved (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E68894E4FFC8A1121" box="[717,808,1806,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
). Connective H-shaped with stem slightly shorter than arms (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6A994E73FE971145" box="[221,309,1842,1868]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft long, bent at near base, nearly parallel to aedeagal base, with a slight dorsal curve at mid-length in lateral view, apex pointed and slightly curved dorsad, gonopore apical (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFF140E6E114E17FB1F1179" box="[1109,1213,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1I–J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
