<subSubSection id="B2A26505FFFE140F6A834FF3FADC1154" pageId="3" pageNumber="347" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FA07368EFFFE140F6A834FF3FADC1154" blockId="3.[151,1436,1678,1921]" pageId="3" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis id="C8CCEA9CFFFE140F6A834FF3FE9910C5" bold="true" box="[199,315,1714,1740]" pageId="3" pageNumber="347">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species described in this paper appears to key out to 
<taxonomicName id="3DB84D0DFFFE140F6E464FF2FBC410C5" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[1026,1126,1714,1741]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Stirellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indrus">
<emphasis id="C8CCEA9CFFFE140F6E464FF2FBC410C5" box="[1026,1126,1714,1741]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="347">S. indrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(couplet 8) in our previous key (See 
<bibRefCitation id="9E294B7FFFFE140F6B474F97FE7B10F8" author="Shah, B. &amp; Naveed, H. &amp; Duan, Y. N." box="[259,473,1750,1777]" pageId="3" pageNumber="347" pagination="398 - 410" refId="ref3956" refString="Shah, B., Naveed, H. &amp; Duan, Y. N. (2020 b) A new species and four new records of Stirellus Osborn &amp; Ball (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Deltocephalinae: Stenometopiini) from Pakistan with a revised key to species. Zootaxa, 4895 (3), 398 - 410. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4895.3.5" type="journal article" year="2020">
Shah 
<emphasis id="C8CCEA9CFFFE140F6B004F96FED510F9" box="[324,375,1750,1776]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="347">et al</emphasis>
., 2020b
</bibRefCitation>
). However it can readily be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="3DB84D0DFFFE140F69B94F96FBC110F9" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[1021,1123,1750,1777]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Stirellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indrus">
<emphasis id="C8CCEA9CFFFE140F69B94F96FBC110F9" box="[1021,1123,1750,1777]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="347">S. indrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the crown with anterior portion black (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFE140F6B7D4FBBFE1C111D" box="[313,446,1786,1812]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="347">Fig. 1A, 1C</figureCitation>
); two conspicuous black spots normally present in middle adjacent to eyes (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFE140F6F4C4FBBFA2F111D" box="[1288,1421,1786,1812]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="347">Fig. 1A, 1C</figureCitation>
); and face black with yellowish patch on frontoclypeus (
<figureCitation id="62832A0BFFFE140F68B54E5FFCEA1131" box="[753,840,1822,1848]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,191,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[151,1436,179,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Stirellus pakistanicus Shah &amp; Duan sp. n. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: head and thorax, dorsal view; D: face; E: male pygofer, lateral view; F: subgenital plate and valve, dorsal view; G: style, dorsal view; H: connective, dorsal view; I: aedeagus, dorsal view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443924/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="347">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Also, the new species has coloration similar to some species described from the Americas (e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="3DB84D0DFFFE140F68284E03FCBE1155" authorityName="Van Duzee" authorityYear="1892" box="[620,796,1858,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Stirellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="C8CCEA9CFFFE140F68284E03FCBE1155" box="[620,796,1858,1884]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="347">Stirellus bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3DB84D0DFFFE140F696D4E03FC7B1155" authorityName="Berg" authorityYear="1879" box="[809,985,1858,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Stirellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picinus">
<emphasis id="C8CCEA9CFFFE140F696D4E03FC7B1155" box="[809,985,1858,1884]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="347">Stirellus picinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
